            <div class="about-text">
                <h3>The Background</h3>
                <p>I am a Computer Science and Data Engineering student at <strong>ENSA Khouribga</strong> with a foundational background rooted deeply in mathematics and system engineering. Before transitioning fully into engineering, I pursued a <em>Licence Fondamentale en Mathématiques et Applications (SMA)</em> at the Faculty of Science in Agadir, and the 42 school Network.</p>

                <h3>Engineering Through a Wider Lens</h3>
                <p>My perspective has continuously evolved with each new experience. My time in the 42 Network fundamentally changed how I view programming, teaching me that understanding core concepts from first principles is what ultimately leads to clean code and robust software.</p>
                <p>This structural mindset deepened further when I dove into machine learning and deep learning; seeing how abstract matrices, vector spaces, and mathematical modeling when fueled by massive data could uncover the intricate patterns of real-world phenomena was the moment I saw mathematics as a powerful human weapon, not just a static, unused tool.</p>

                <p>This background gives me the opportunity to discover and dig deep into three main areas:</p>
                <ul class="about-list">
                    <li><strong>Data Engineering:</strong> Dealing with data architecture, understanding how it moves end-to-end, and building highly reliable pipelines.</li>
                    <li><strong>Software Engineering:</strong> Designing clean, scalable system architectures and writing highly optimized code from the ground up.</li>
                    <li><strong>ML & Deep Learning:</strong> Implementing algorithmic models to map complex real-world variables.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Everything you find on this website intersects with these three domains. Even when a topic seems purely mathematical, it is the exact kind of math I manually leverage to build and develop my models.</p>

                <h3>Purpose of This Space</h3>
                <p>This platform is both a professional index of my capabilities and an active, open-source technical notebook. My documentations kept private for a long time, and I thought why not to share it, as it is at least my first go-to reference.</p>
                <p>These documentations are divided into two main sections:</p>
                <ul class="about-list">
                    <li><strong><a href="/projects">Projects</a>:</strong> Concrete proof of execution. This section showcases engineered software solutions for various technical challenges, where I break down exactly how I built them and why they were engineered the way they were.</li>
                    <li><strong><a href="/articles">Articles</a>:</strong> Technical documentation stripped of fluff. I write about the complex concepts I encounter across computer science and engineering, focusing entirely on logic, core intuition, and hands-on implementation.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
